⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Almanacs
node N1 · N1 · ⟦The Almanacs:N1:83a65d⟧

WHO   — The Almanacs — the maker of the year ahead
WHAT  — The working trade of the seer of Salon — month-by-month predictions printed for each new year, and the true source of his fame in his own lifetime, more than the Centuries were then.
WHERE — N1 · Nostradamus  Framework inputs: Les Almanachs et Présages (1550–1566)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a man must eat, and a prophet must be read; because the people wanted the weather and the wheat-price and the fate of kings; because the almanac was the newspaper, the horoscope, and the farmer's calendar all at once.
HOW   — By judicial astrology — the positions of the planets read month against month — dressed in the same allusive, ominous verse that made his name; sold cheap, printed yearly, devoured and discarded.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I sold the year ahead a month at a time — weather and war and wheat — and that, not the Centuries, was how my own age knew my name.

spoken token : ryl-thys-din   ·   hex : 83a65d
